Primitive data types: int, double,char, boolean

Declaring variables: Integer 
Java   : int i =10 or int i; i=10
we can assign the value of i during declaration or we can declare i type and assign value to i anytime
Python   :i=10
We dont have to declare

Declaring variable : Long
Java 
long y = 123456L
Python
No such data type

Declaring variable : float
Java
float u = 12.4f
Python
u = 2.3

Declaring variable: double
Java
double a = 12.33
double b = 100;   /*tis will be treated as 100.00*/
Python
No such data type

Declaring vaariable:Charecter
Java
char r='a' /*charecters are represented in single quotes*/
char e='1' /*integer can me converted as charecter*/
Python
u = 'P' or "i"

Declaring variable:boolean
Java
boolean b1=true;
boolean b2=false;
true & false are values as well as keywords
Python
res = True
res = False

Declaring variable:String
Java
String O = "Hello"
String t = "100"
String is not a data type it is a class. String is denoted by double quotes
Python
x = "Hello World"

Programs:Java
1.
class Main {   
   public static void main(String args[]) {      
         int t;      
         System.out.println(t); 
    }   
}

Sol:prog.java:4: error: variable t might not have been initialized
		System.out.println(t); 
Unlike class members, local variables of methods must be assigned a value to before they are accessed, or it is a compile error.

2.
class Test
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        Double object = new Double("2.4");
        int a = object.intValue();
        byte b = object.byteValue();
        float d = object.floatValue();
        double c = object.doubleValue();
 
        System.out.println(a + b + c + d );
 
    }
}
Sol:8.800000095367432
